news.title: Gurugram DC allows two housing colonies to install 11 gates on internal roads
news.para: Police are yet to approve the other applications, due to which no decision has been taken yet on installation of gates in BPTP Astaire Garden and Experion colony off Dwarka Expressway.

news.title: Housing sales in top seven cities record 14% rise in Q1 2024: Anarock
news.para: MMR and Hyderabad saw the maximum new supply, accounting for 51% of the total new launches across the top seven cities. Hyderabad saw a 57% yearly increase in new supply in Q1 2024, while MMR saw its new supply decline by 9% in the period.

news.title: Shree Cement invests over Rs 2,500 crore to set up cement plant in Guntur
news.para: Built with an investment of Rs 2,500 crore, the Guntur plant will be Shree Cement's sixth integrated production facility in the country.

news.title: Gurugram: Safety & pollution key concerns ahead of demolition at Chintels Paradiso
news.para: According to a senior official, the key concerns about demolition of five towers — D, E, F, G and H —in Sector 109 township are pollution, disaster management and fire safety among others.

news.title: SWAMIH, Nisus Finance invest Rs 465 crore in two housing projects
news.para: Nisus and SWAMIH Fund invested in Aliens Developers' projects, with Nisus focusing on structured capital. The SWAMIH Fund initiative, introduced by Nirmala Sitharaman, aims to address stalled housing projects.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto decline by 1.1% in March
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales declined 1.1% in March from the previous month after falling 11.5% in February, according to Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB) data.

news.title: Canada PM launches $6 billion fund to quell housing crisis
news.para: Canada faces a housing affordability crisis as a rapidly increasing immigrant population has far outpaced the number of available homes, leading to increases in prices and rents. High inflation and 22-year high interest rates have also driven up mortgage costs.

news.title: Civic bodies in Uttar Pradesh collects revenue worth Rs 3,102 crore in FY24
news.para: Lucknow and Kanpur achieved remarkable revenue growth through technology-based solutions. The urban local bodies implemented innovative schemes to boost revenue, with Lucknow leading in revenue collection.

news.title: Jaipur civic body collects urban development tax worth Rs 147 crore in FY24
news.para: The municipal corporation collected a revenue of Rs 56 crore by auctioning advertising sites in financial year 2023-24, which is around 80% more than the previous financial year.

news.title: Rajkot builder booked for selling six plots without partners' knowledge
news.para: The complaint was filed by Jayant Chavda at the Paddadhri police station on Monday naming Shailesh Kamaliya, Chavda stated that he, along with Bisu Vala and the Kamaliya, purchased land in a village in Paddadhri taluka in 2010.

news.title: NGT fines Mohali development body over lapses in housing project
news.para: The NGT observed that Gmada failed to file a satisfactory reply to the show-cause notice issued by the SEIAA over non-compliance of environmental clearance norms at Purab Premium Apartments (PPA) project in Sector 88, Mohali.

news.title: HC directs state government to appoint Karnataka REAT chairperson
news.para: Pointing out that proceedings are going on since January 22, Justice M Nagaprasanna directed the state govt to do the needful before April 15.

news.title: Calcutta high court orders demolition of 14 illegal buildings in Narkeldanga
news.para: A KMC buildings department source said, out of the 14 buildings, two were permanent, concrete structures and the rest were huts, While hearing a petition, Justice Amrita Sinha ordered the civic body to conduct a spot inspection.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body's initiative to install 75,000 LED streetlights faces delay
news.para: Now, with the directive to issue new tenders, HDMC awaits instructions from the directorate of municipal administration (DMA) to commence a fresh tender process.

news.title: Delhi civic body collects property tax worth Rs 2,137 crore in FY24
news.para: MCD's property tax collection in FY 2023-24 decreased by 11.5% to ₹2,137 crore. The number of taxpayers reduced to 12.6 lakh. No amnesty scheme led to the decline, disappointing officials like Vibha Sharma and Raja Iqbal Singh.

news.title: Shriram Properties receives penalty order amounting to Rs 446.79 crore
news.para: Shriram Properties said that this penalty order is pertaining to a matter which is already pending before the Madras High Court for which the court has already passed an order directing the department to maintain the ‘status quo’.

news.title: Warburg Pincus frontrunner to buy Shriram Housing Finance
news.para: Negotiations are ongoing with both seeking to maximise value, “but for the moment, Warburg seems a more aggressive suitor or bidder for the company,” said a person close to the company on condition of anonymity.

news.title: Gurugram civic body makes self-certification mandatory for property registration
news.para: Property owners can self-certify the data on the govt portal property.ulbharyana.gov.in. They will have to pay outstanding dues, if any, and obtain a no-objection certificate (NOC), which is already mandatory for registration of properties.

news.title: Cement companies set to hike prices from April onwards
news.para: Cement prices set to rise despite demand slowdown before elections. Analysts warn of margin contraction. Price hikes vary by region, with southern India experiencing substantial increases.

news.title: Bombay HC sends Yash Builders' proprietor to three months' civil imprisonment
news.para: The builder, as stated by Justice Abhay Ahuja, willfully breached undertakings given to the High Court and was absent on several dates, thereby interfering with the administration of justice.
